# New Tenant Onboarding — Minimal Data & Dev Smoke Test

Use this rule when onboarding a **new `tenant_id`** (local Docker dev **or** prod satellite). It hardens the **minimum database rows**, **test admin login**, **logo/contact**, and **verification** steps so a site can sign in, see the Admin menu, and open `/admin`.

**Parent / sibling rules (do not duplicate):**

| Rule | Role |
|------|------|
| [satellite_domain_new_site_configuration_and_deployment.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/satellite_domain_new_site_configuration_and_deployment.mdc) | **Prod satellite** Phases 0–8 (DNS, Amplify, Clerk, CORS) — runbook `#phase0` |
| [database_local_postgres_connectivity.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/database_local_postgres_connectivity.mdc) | Local Docker Postgres (`event_site_manager_db`, container `event_site_manager_db-postgresql-1`) |
| [clerk_auth_admin_user_lookup_avatar.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/clerk_auth_admin_user_lookup_avatar.mdc) | Admin menu = `user_role` ADMIN; `/api/auth/admin-status` |
| [user_profile_operations.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/user_profile_operations.mdc) | Profile auto-create on sign-in (defaults to MEMBER) |
| [database_schema_guidelines.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/database_schema_guidelines.mdc) | Table/column naming |

**Canonical HTML (prod):** [satellite-frontend-deployment-guide.html](mdc:documentation/aws-infrastructure/satellite-frontend-deployment-guide.html) `#phase0`, `#deployed-instance-giventa`

