## When to apply

- New `NEXT_PUBLIC_TENANT_ID` in a frontend `.env.local` / `.env.production`
- Satellite Phase 0 gate — org/settings missing for tenant
- Local dev: API on `http://localhost:8080`, user signed in but **no Admin menu**
- First-time bootstrap after copying admin backend into a marketing site (e.g. `giventa-site`)

---

## Phase order (agent checklist)

```
0. Agree tenant_id + www hostname + test user email
1. tenant_organization     (required first — FK parent for emails)
2. tenant_settings         (homepage flags, contact, logo URL)
3. tenant_email_addresses  (CONTACT + INFO minimum for forms/email jobs)
4. satellite_domains       (prod only — Phase 5 of satellite rule; optional for local)
5. Test user sign-in       (Clerk creates user_profile as MEMBER)
6. Promote test user ADMIN (UPDATE — not INSERT duplicate)
7. Smoke verify            (API + UI)
```

**Gate:** Do not start Route 53 / Amplify / Clerk satellite DNS until steps 1–3 pass on the **target API** (local or prod). See satellite rule Phase 0.

---

## Step 0 — Collect inputs (ask operator)

| Input | Example | Used in |
|-------|---------|---------|
| `tenant_id` | `giventa_inc_3` | All tables, `NEXT_PUBLIC_TENANT_ID` |
| `www` hostname | `www.giventa.com` | `tenant_organization.domain`, satellite_domains |
| Organization name | `Giventa Inc` | `tenant_organization.organization_name` |
| Contact email | `giventauser@gmail.com` | org, settings, test admin, tenant_email_addresses |
| Contact phone | `+1 312-343-0073` | settings / org |
| Logo URL (HTTPS) | S3 or `/globex/assets/images/logo.png` | `tenant_organization.logo_url`, `tenant_settings.logo_image_url` |
| Test Clerk user | Same contact email | Sign in on primary or satellite |

**Google Calendar:** There is **no tenant-level Google Calendar ID** in the database. Event pages build **per-event** “Add to Google Calendar” links from `event_details.start_date` / `end_date` in the frontend. Smoke test = create one event with future dates and click the calendar link.

**MinIO / media:** Production media uses **AWS S3** (`eventapp-media-bucket`). Local admin media upload requires the Spring Boot stack running and valid AWS (or configured storage) credentials in the backend `.env` — not a separate MinIO tenant row. Minimal onboarding = set `logo_image_url` to a reachable HTTPS URL; defer bulk media until S3 is configured.

